'''Mofussil''' is an Indian-English term used widely in the Indian subcontinent In [[Tamil Nadu]], [[India]] the term refers to suburban and rural areas, especially to transportation services to such areas.

In [[Bangladesh]], '''mofussil''' refers to the regions outside the major cities of [[Dhaka]] and [[Chittagong]]. This can indicate either the secondary cities ([[Rajshahi]], [[Khulna]], etc), the small semi-rural towns and also the villages. Although value-neutral, the word occasionally carries negative connotations when used by residents of the large metropolises, similar to ''the boonies'' or ''the sticks'' in [[English]]. ''X is a mofussil boy'' is one example of usage. 


